This paper deals with the deployment of a hybrid cellular network to reduce RF pollution and enhance spectral efficiency. It discusses the use of multi-layer overlaid hierarchical structures for macro, micro, pico, and femto cells. This topic falls under the domain of network infrastructure and wireless communication, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the optimization of available resources through remote technologies, which could be related to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the concern over health hazards caused by base stations could be related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
